news.title: Bidhannagar civic body sends revised property tax bills to Salt Lake homes
news.para: Civic authorities said that till date they had been collecting property tax on old rates based on the old valuation which was very low compared to the rising cost and civic services which BMC provides.

news.title: Not feasible for government to give land ownership to slum dwellers: Experts
news.para: The state has around 582 dwellings which house more than 7.7 lakh people, majority of which are on private land. As per a report from 2016, there are 128 such clusters in Dehradun district among which 70 were on private land.

news.title: Chandigarh: Demolition drive notices put up outside two colonies
news.para: Notice boards have been installed outside the colonies and the authority has started daily public announcement (Munadi) on an almost daily basis to inform people to vacate the area. While the exact date of the drive is yet to be finalised, sources said that it will be held in a few weeks.

news.title: Noida: Four illegal flats, eight shops razed in Shahberi
news.para: Prabhat Shankar, manager (work circle 1) of Greater Noida Authority, said during an inspection some people were found involved in unauthorised constructions in the area.

news.title: Government may extend PMAY scheme in urban areas for two more years
news.para: The scheme to provide pucca roof to every family in urban areas, the PMAY scheme was launched in June 2015 and the government had initially set March 2022 as the deadline.

news.title: HC verdict on GST on under-construction flats to reduce tax outgo for buyers: Experts
news.para: ​Currently, GST is levied on sale of under-construction flats/units wherein the entire value of flat or unit (including value of underlying land) is taxed after giving Ad Hoc deduction of 1/3 of value of flat/unit towards land irrespective of actual value of land.

news.title: Don't allow dilution of RERA being 'custodian' of law, advisory council to housing ministry
news.para: The minutes of the meeting of the CAC has now been put in the public domain at a time when the Supreme Court has set the May 15 timeline for Centre and states to submit all details of the rules by them and to submit whether these are in accordance with the Central rules.

news.title: Shipping Corporation of India to hive off realty assets
news.para: "The demerger process of Shipping Corporation of India (SCI) is on. We are going to hive off all the real estate of the company. So they will not be part of the privatisation process," a senior government official told ET.

news.title: Land acquisition in NCR getting difficult for developers
news.para: This comes at a time when demand for new homes has picked up after the Covid-19-led slump and most units in under-construction and completed projects have already been sold.

news.title: Aurangabad: No eviction relief for Labour Colony residents from HC
news.para: On May 6, the two-member bench comprising Justice R D Dhanuka and Justice S G Mehare directed the petitioners and other occupants of the colony to hand over “peaceful and vacant possession” of their respective structures to the Aurangabad collector on or before 11 am on May 10.

news.title: Tamil Nadu introduces apartment redevelopment bill
news.para: Introducing the Tamil Nadu Apartment Ownership Bill, 2022, housing minister S Muthusamy said “The new legislation was introduced to safeguard the interest of the apartment owners as well as improve the administration of common areas and facilities.”

news.title: Over Rs 2,160 crore collected as stamp duty in Raigad district
news.para: ​As per figures made available by the assistant collector of stamp duty collection, the target for the year was Rs 1,880 crore, which was surpassed.

news.title: Macrotech to invest Rs 3,800 crore in FY23 on construction of realty projects: MD
news.para: Macrotech Developers MD and CEO Abhishek Lodha said: "We spent about Rs 2,600 crore on construction last fiscal year. Our construction spend is estimated at Rs 3,800 crore during the current fiscal."

news.title: HDFC hikes lending rate by 30 bps
news.para: "HDFC increases its Retail Prime Lending Rate (RPLR) on housing loans, on which its Adjustable Rate Home Loans (ARHL) are benchmarked, by 30 basis points, with effect from May 9, 2022," the housing finance company said in a statement.

news.title: Indian Bank revises repo linked lending rate
news.para: The bank's move comes after a number of banks raised their external benchmark based lending rates following an increase of 0.40 per cent in the repo rate -- at which the Reserve Bank lends short term money to banks.
